# Driver package is byte-exact: SONR_WinUSB.cat stores the SHA-256 of the .inf bytes.
# If git ever normalizes the .inf line endings (CRLF->LF), the hash stops matching the signed
# catalog and pnputil fails with 0x800B0100 "hash not present in catalog". Treat as binary.
*.inf   -text
*.cat   -text
*.cer   -text
*.bin   -text
*.mobileconfig -text

# The WebUSB policy .reg is UTF-16LE; never touch its bytes either.
*.reg   -text
